"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528105","Home Office","false","2016-06-28","<p>The Home Office will not necessarily be aware that a woman is pregnant unless she chooses to make this known to us and a woman may not know herself that she is pregnant when she is detained. It may not always be appropriate for healthcare professionals to disclose information that the patient has asked not to be disclosed.</p><p>Subject to these limitations, management information for 21 June 2016 shows that there were no pregnant women detained under Immigration Act powers at Yarl's Wood immigration removal centre.</p><p>Information on the number of pregnant women deported from the UK in each of the last five years is not held centrally and providing it would incur disproportionate cost.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","40991","2016-06-28T13:20:21.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528105/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528105/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528105/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-06-20","Yarl's Wood Immigration Removal Centre: Pregnancy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many pregnant women are in detention at Yarl's Wood immigration removal centre.","false","Biography information for Angela Crawley","Lanark and Hamilton East","Angela Crawley","40861"
