"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528108","Home Office","false","2016-07-04","<p>The Home Office is responsible, along with the Ministry of Justice, for negotiating EU legislation in the Justice and Home Affairs area. The Home Office provides Explanatory Memoranda to Parliament on any proposals defined by the terms of reference of the parliamentary EU scrutiny committees, which can be found online.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2016-07-04T13:23:58.777Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528108/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528108/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528108/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-06-20","Home Office: EU Action","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, which EU (a) legislative and (b) other proposals her Department is leading negotiations on for the Government in the Council of the EU.","false","Biography information for John Redwood","Wokingham","John Redwood","40909"
