"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528136","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-06-30","<p>The legal profession in England and Wales is independent from government. We want to see an innovative and competitive market that provides people with affordable legal services that they want and need, with regulation that supports the public and consumer interest.</p><p> </p><p>We welcome the Law Society’s survey and will take account of the findings as part of the development of legal services policy.</p><p> </p><p>The legal services regulators have a duty to promote the regulatory objectives set out in the Legal Services Act 2007, including improving access to justice and increasing public understanding of the citizen's legal rights and duties. The regulators have established the “Legal Choices” website, which provides people with information to help them in deciding whether and how to seek legal advice and the available services they might choose from. The Advicenow website, established by Law for Life, provides information on rights and the law.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara","40869 ; 40870","2016-06-30T15:34:12.503Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528136/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528136/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528136/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-06-20","Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what steps his Department is taking to improve legal education in England and Wales.","false","Biography information for Christina Rees","Neath","Christina Rees","40871"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528137","Northern Ireland Office","false","2016-07-01","<p>The Department is not responsible for leading any negotiations at the EU Council.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2016-07-01T10:58:56.013Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528137/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528137/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528137/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2016-06-20","Northern Ireland Office: EU Action","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, which EU (a) legislative and (b) other proposals her Department is leading negotiations on for the Government in the Council of the EU.","false","Biography information for John Redwood","Wokingham","John Redwood","40912"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528138","Northern Ireland Office","false","2016-07-01","<p>There are no EU directives related to the Department’s responsibilities awaiting transposition into UK law.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2016-07-01T11:00:19.11Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528138/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528138/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528138/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2016-06-20","Northern Ireland Office: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what EU directives related to her Department's responsibilities are awaiting transposition into UK law.","false","Biography information for John Redwood","Wokingham","John Redwood","40892"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528139","Scotland Office","false","2016-06-30","<p>The Scotland Office has no EU Directives awaiting transposition into UK law.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2016-06-30T14:18:16.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528139/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528139/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528139/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2016-06-20","Scotland Office: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what EU directives related to his Department's responsibilities are awaiting transposition into UK law.","false","Biography information for John Redwood","Wokingham","John Redwood","40893"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528140","Scotland Office","false","2016-06-30","<p>The Scotland Office is not leading negotiations on any EU legislation or any other proposals for the UK Government in the Council of the European Union.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2016-06-30T14:19:39.973Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528140/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528140/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528140/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2016-06-20","Scotland Office: EU Action","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, which EU (a) legislative and (b) other proposals his Department is leading negotiations on for the Government in the Council of the EU.","false","Biography information for John Redwood","Wokingham","John Redwood","40913"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528141","Scotland Office","false","2016-06-29","<p>I am due to meet the Minister for Immigration soon to discuss a range of issues. Officials from the Scotland Office are in regular contact with officials from the Home Office on a range of issues concerning asylum seekers in Scotland, including asylum seeker dispersal policy.</p><p> </p><p>The Home Office is currently in direct discussions with the Convention of Scottish Local Authorities and a number of local authorities on how asylum dispersal will continue to work in practice. The Home Office maintains an active partnership with local government across the UK, including those in Scotland, and funds Strategic Migration Partnerships to plan for the most appropriate dispersal of asylum seekers. The partnerships consider the impact on communities and local services so that adjustments to dispersal patterns can be made where appropriate.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2016-06-29T12:00:59.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528141/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528141/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528141/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2016-06-20","Asylum: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, pursuant to the Answer of 9 June 2016 to Question 38918, what discussions he has had with the Home Secretary on asylum seeker dispersal policy in Scotland since December 2015.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","40967"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528142","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-29","<p>We are encouraging SMEs, new entrants and innovators to work with the industry to identify and take advantage of initiatives benefitting the supply chain and improving access to the market to ensure that the UK remains competitive and develops the capacity for orders at home and abroad. It should be noted that over 2,000 railway vehicles are currently on order (being manufactured or to be manufactured) in the UK.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-06-29T13:41:47.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528142/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528142/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528142/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-20","Trains: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that British manufacturers have fair access to the tendering process to promote the use of UK parts in foreign-made railway trains on the UK rail network.","false","Biography information for Karen Lumley","Redditch","Karen Lumley","40966"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528143","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-30","<p>The Department has published three impact assessments relating to the provisions contained in the Bus Services Bill. Those documents include our analysis of the expected effects of the Bus Services Bill.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-06-30T10:31:45.553Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528143/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528143/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528143/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-20","Bus Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 13 June 2016 to Question 39847, what effect he expects the provisions of the Bus Services Bill to have on his Department's estimates of future trips by mode.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","40987"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528144","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-29","<p>As you have indicated the winning bid will be awarded to the most economically advantageous tender as set out in section 7 of the Invitation to Tender (ITT). This is determined through a combination of ‘price’ and weighted quality points awarded as part of the Department’s evaluation of initiatives proposed by a bidder to meet or exceed the Department’s requirements set out in each delivery plan at section 5 of the East Anglia ITT.</p><p> </p><p>It is in the delivery plans themselves that references to social characteristics are included. In the main they appear in the Stations, Customer Experience and Leadership delivery plans.</p><p> </p><p>In respect of Rolling Stock, as a minimum, the Department has required that bidders propose either new rolling stock or non-new build rolling stock. If non-new build rolling stock, passengers will perceive the overall design, internal ambience, condition and facilities, and the external condition, as being modern, comfortable and comparable to that of new or nearly new rolling stock.</p><p> </p><p>This link takes you to the full ITT should you require it: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/461470/east-anglia-invitation-to-tender.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/461470/east-anglia-invitation-to-tender.pdf</a></p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-06-29T09:26:57.217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528144/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528144/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528144/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-20","Railways: East of England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, with reference to section 7 of the East Anglia franchise Invitation to Tender, published on 17 September 2015, what weighting his Department has ascribed to (a) social characteristics and (b) other factors used to determine the most economically advantageous tender for (i) that franchise and (ii) proposals for new rolling stock orders by bidders for that franchise.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","41049"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528145","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-29","<p>Poole Borough Council received funding for the LSTF 2011-15 programme as a partner authority which was led by Dorset County Council for the ‘School Travel Health Check’ project; they also received funding for the ‘Be SMArT’ project led by Bournemouth Borough Council. Both projects aimed to facilitate sustainable travel and included improvements for cycling.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>The Department is also preparing to launch the Access Fund for revenue only funding, which will be open to all local authorities in England (excluding London) regardless of previous bidding success. This will include an objective to actively promote increased levels of physical activity through walking and cycling.</p><p> </p><p>The Access Fund is being aligned with the third Local Growth Deal which presents opportunities for all authorities to seek capital funding for their sustainable transport schemes. All local authorities have been notified to engage with their Local Enterprise Partnerships and the Department on both these opportunities.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-06-29T13:12:56.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528145/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528145/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528145/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-20","Cycling: Poole","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps his Department is taking to increase cycling provision in Poole.","false","Biography information for Michael Tomlinson","Mid Dorset and North Poole","Michael Tomlinson","41043"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528146","Department for Transport","false","2016-07-01","<p><strong> </strong></p><p>The proportion of flights between UK airports and oil rigs undertaken by the AS3332 SUPER PUMA and Eurocopter EC225 aircraft in each year since 2007 is as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Aircraft Type</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2007</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2008</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2009</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2010</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2011</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>AEROSPATIALE AS332 SUPER PUMA C1E</p></td><td><p>54.1%</p></td><td><p>42.5%</p></td><td><p>33.4%</p></td><td><p>28.7%</p></td><td><p>24.9%</p></td><td><p>23.5%</p></td><td><p>25.9%</p></td><td><p>13.4%</p></td><td><p>4.0%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>EUROCOPTER EC225 (H225)</p></td><td><p>11.0%</p></td><td><p>14.6%</p></td><td><p>17.2%</p></td><td><p>23.4%</p></td><td><p>27.2%</p></td><td><p>21.0%</p></td><td><p>1.5%</p></td><td><p>15.8%</p></td><td><p>21.4%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><em> </em></p><p><em> </em></p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-07-01T09:31:56.813Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528146/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528146/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528146/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-20","Offshore Industry: Helicopters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 14 June 2016 to Question 39766, what proportion of all flights between UK airports and oil rigs were undertaken by (a) AS332 Super Puma and (b) Eurocopter EC225 aircraft in each of those years.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","41041"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528147","Department for Transport","false","2016-07-01","<p>The proportion of flights between UK airports and oil rigs undertaken by helicopters other than AS3332 SUPER PUMA and Eurocopter EC225 aircraft in each year since 2007 is in the attached table.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-07-01T09:23:19.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528147/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528147/answer","UIN 41040 - Table.pdf","Table","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528147/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-20","Offshore Industry: Helicopters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 14 June 2016 to Question 39766, on offshore industry helicopters, how many and what proportion of flights in the UK North Sea oil and gas sector were undertaken by each other licensed model helicopter in each year since 2007.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","41040"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528148","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-29","<p>The Driver and Vehicle Standards Agency (DVSA) forecasts the demand for all types of driving tests including motorcycle tests; this is done annually and reviewed quarterly. The information is used to ensure the Agency has the required number of motorcycle examiners available in order to meet its commitment of maintaining an annual six week waiting time.</p><p> </p><p>Demand for tests has increased over the last three years and DVSA has responded by conducting 6,000 more test per year, as shown below.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>M1</p></td><td><p>M2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>46,263</p></td><td><p>43,475</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>52,005</p></td><td><p>49,194</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015/16 YTD</p></td><td><p>46,150</p></td><td><p>44,068</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p>Demand for motorcycle tests is seasonal; during the Summer months (April to September) DVSA increases test availability by opening summer work patterns.</p><p> </p><p>Last year the Agency achieved motorcycle test waiting times of 4.7 weeks for module one and 3.9 weeks for module two. Waiting times are currently 7 weeks for module one and 5.8 weeks for module two.</p><p> </p><p>As part of DVSA’s current recruitment campaign it is seeking to recruit 16 fast track motorcycle examiners. There are also currently four fast track biker recruits undergoing new entrant training.</p><p> </p><p>Training has also been scheduled to provide a further 14 bike examiners before September (this includes two currently attending and 12 more booked on to the training course).</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-06-29T12:36:43.64Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528148/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528148/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528148/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-20","Motorcycles: Driving Tests","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps his Department has taken to increase the availability of practical test appointments for motorcycle drivers.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","41000"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528149","Department for Transport","false","2016-07-04","<p>There has not been an assessment made of the effect of the EU Third Directive on Driving Licences (2006/126/EC) on the motorcycle assessment industry.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-07-04T13:27:34.353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528149/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528149/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528149/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-20","Driving: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment his Department has made of the effect of the EU Third Directive on Driving Licenses on the motorcycle assessment industry.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","41001"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528150","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-29","<p>The Driver and Vehicle Standards Agency (DVSA) evaluates the effectiveness of its examiner training programme by monitoring the waiting times for both modules of the motorcycle practical test. This enables the agency to balance the demand for tests with the number of motorcycle examiners, which directly affects the availability of motorcycle test appointments. This is measured against the agency’s commitment to maintain or improve upon a six-week annual average waiting time for practical motorcycle tests.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, the progress against this commitment, the demand for tests and the examiner training programme are discussed in a wider forum at a monthly Service Management Group for Vocational and Motorcycle testing. Specific issues are escalated in this forum as necessary.</p><p> </p><p>Waiting times for last year and the first two months of this year are shown in the table below, it should be noted that motorcycle testing is affected by seasonal variation and waiting times inevitably rise in the summer months when demand is higher.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Commitment: 6 weeks</p></td><td><p>Year 2015/16</p></td><td><p>Year to Date April - May 2016</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>MC Mod 1</p></td><td><p>4.7</p></td><td><p>6.8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>MC Mod 2</p></td><td><p>3.9</p></td><td><p>5.5</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-06-29T11:06:21.863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528150/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528150/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528150/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-20","Driver and Vehicle Standards Agency: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment his Department has made of the effectiveness of the Driver and Vehicle Standards Agency training programme in increasing availability of motorcycle assessors.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","41002"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528151","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-30","<p>The Cycling and Walking Investment Strategy contains a target to double cycling by 2025 and an objective to increase walking activity. We are currently consulting on a programme of activity to work towards these increases.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-06-30T12:07:56.683Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528151/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528151/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528151/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-20","Cycling and Walking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 13 June 2016 to Question 39847, what assessment he has made of the effect of the cycling and walking investment strategy on his Department's estimates of future trips by mode.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","40997"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528152","Department for Transport","false","2016-07-01","<p>Disability awareness training is vital for equipping bus drivers with the knowledge and skills to provide all passengers with the assistance they need, and I am grateful to the industry for ensuring that the majority of drivers can now benefit from it.</p><p> </p><p>Evidence from the Confederation of Passenger Transport (CPT), published in “Summary of responses to the Department for Transport's review of the mandatory disability awareness training exemption applied under EU Regulation 181/2011 (concerning bus and coach passenger rights)” (<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/bus-and-coach-drivers-summary-of-disability-awareness-training-review" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/bus-and-coach-drivers-summary-of-disability-awareness-training-review</a> ) in January 2015 estimates that between 2008 and 2013 153,357 drivers undertook disability awareness training as part of their Certificate of Professional Competence, compared to the 130,000 drivers understood to be active in the industry. It is to this that I believe my Hon Friend was referring in her response of the 11<sup>th</sup> June 2015.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-07-01T10:29:16.023Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528152/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528152/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528152/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-20","Bus Services: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, with reference to the oral contribution of the Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Transport of 11 June 2015, Official Report, column 1310, what the evidential basis is for the statement that almost 100 per cent of bus drivers have received some form of disability awareness training.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","40998"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528153","Department for Transport","false","2016-07-04","<p>My Department is responsible for EU transport measures relating to Aviation, Roads, Maritime and Railways and other cross modal dossiers.</p><p> </p><p>The Department provides Explanatory Memoranda to Parliament on any proposals defined by the terms of reference of the parliamentary EU scrutiny committee.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-07-04T16:18:45.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528153/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528153/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528153/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-20","Department for Transport: EU Action","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, which EU (a) legislative and (b) other proposals his Department is leading negotiations on for the Government in the Council of the EU.","false","Biography information for John Redwood","Wokingham","John Redwood","40914"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528154","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-29","<p>The draft Cycling and Walking Investment Strategy was published in March and set out the Department’s targets for cycling. This included an objective to reduce the rate of cyclists killed or seriously injured on England’s roads, measured as the number of fatalities and serious injuries per billion miles cycled, each year.</p><p> </p><p>We are in the process of analysing feedback received during the consultation and expect to publish the final Strategy this summer.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-06-29T13:31:40.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528154/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528154/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/528154/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-20","Cycling: Accidents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will introduce measurable targets on reducing the number of cyclists killed or seriously injured.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","40872"
