"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525550","HM Treasury","false","2016-06-29","<p>The references to ‘handicapped’ people in Schedule 8 to the Value Added Tax Act 1994 are being considered alongside some other outdated terms that are used in the Schedule. This work will be taken forward carefully to ensure there are no unintended consequences as the terminology carries meaning that is derived from and interacts with other UK legislation.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-06-29T12:58:28.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525550/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525550/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525550/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-06-15","Value Added Tax Act 1994","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will bring forward legislative proposals to revise references to handicapped people in Schedule 8 to the Value Added Tax Act 1994.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","40740"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525551","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-06-29","<p>Ministers in the Department for Communities and Local Government meet members of minority communities on a regular basis. My officials are happy to meet with representatives of the British Alevi community and discuss items that have been raised by the All-Party Parliamentary Group for Alevis.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2016-06-29T14:30:58.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525551/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525551/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525551/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-06-15","Alevism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what plans his Department has to engage with representatives from the Alevi community in Britain.","false","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","40794"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525552","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-07-01","<p>Officials in my Department keep accurate official records in line with Cabinet Office guidance and in accordance with business needs.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2016-07-01T13:37:20.38Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525552/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525552/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525552/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-06-15","Department for Communities and Local Government: Domestic Visits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 14 June 2016 to Question 39438, if his Department will keep an annual record of locations visited by Ministers and officials of his Department in the future; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","40722"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525553","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-06-29","<p>The Government believes social tenants on higher incomes should contribute a fairer level of rent. More than 90 percent of tenants will be unaffected by our plans. Many above the threshold will be protected from big rent rises through our tapered approach.</p><p>All of Bradford’s council housing stock was transferred to housing association control in 2003. The policy is voluntary for housing associations so it would be for the housing association managing the stock to decide whether to operate a pay to stay approach.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-06-29T14:26:58.6Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525553/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525553/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525553/answer","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525553/answer/previousversion/5014","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-06-15","Social Rented Housing: Bradford","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether his Department has made an estimate of the number of families in Bradford who will move home as a result of pay to stay provisions of the Housing and Planning Act 2016 during the current Parliament.","false","Biography information for Judith Cummins","Bradford South","Judith Cummins","40687"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525554","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-06-29","<p>Under the voluntary agreement with the National Housing Federation and housing associations, every home sold to tenants will result in an additional home being provided. This will lead to an increase in overall housing supply.</p><p>The voluntary agreement states that housing associations and the Government share a mutual objective to ensure that replacement homes are delivered as quickly as possible. Whilst aiming for replacement within two years, the default position is that housing associations will have flexibility to replace homes within a three year period.</p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-06-29T14:24:52.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525554/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525554/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525554/answer","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525554/answer/previousversion/5015","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-06-15","Right to Buy Scheme: Housing Associations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment he has made of the replacement rate of housing association properties sold through right-to-buy in each year since the launch of that policy; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","40701"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525555","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-06-29","<p>There are no plans to change a Local Authority's ability to propose conditions that meet the policy tests in the National Planning Policy Framework; including conditions related to archaeology and wildlife. The Neighbourhood Planning and Infrastructure Bill will include measures to ensure that pre-commencement planning conditions are only imposed where they are absolutely necessary.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-06-29T14:26:08.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525555/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525555/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525555/answer","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525555/answer/previousversion/5016","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-06-15","Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether the Government plans to bring forward proposals in the Neighbourhood and Planning and Infrastructure Bill to remove the requirement for developers to carry out archaeological and wildlife surveys before starting housing projects.","false","Biography information for Gordon Henderson","Sittingbourne and Sheppey","Gordon Henderson","40705"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525556","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-06-27","<p>Details of Ministerial meetings with external organisations are published on a quarterly basis and can be accessed via the gov.uk website.</p><p> </p>","Bexleyheath and Crayford","David Evennett",,"2016-06-27T14:37:38.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525556/answer","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525556/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525556/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-06-15","Gambling: Internet","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what discussions he has had with the Gambling Commission and the Remote Gambling Association in the last 12 months on the progress of the online multi-operator self-exclusion scheme.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","40753"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525557","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-06-27","<p>All individual gambling operators are required by their licence conditions to put in place procedures for self-exclusion.</p><p> </p><p>In May 2015, the Gambling Commission introduced a new licence condition which also requires online gambling operators, other than certain society lottery operators, to participate in a national online self-exclusion scheme once it is developed and available.</p><p> </p><p>The Remote Gambling Association (RGA) is currently developing the online multi-operator self-exclusion scheme on behalf of the online sector.</p>","Bexleyheath and Crayford","David Evennett","40755","2016-06-27T14:39:17.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525557/answer","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525557/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525557/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-06-15","Gambling: Internet","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what progress has been made on the development of the multi-operator self-exclusion scheme since 17 February 2016.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","40754"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525558","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-06-27","<p>All individual gambling operators are required by their licence conditions to put in place procedures for self-exclusion.</p><p> </p><p>In May 2015, the Gambling Commission introduced a new licence condition which also requires online gambling operators, other than certain society lottery operators, to participate in a national online self-exclusion scheme once it is developed and available.</p><p> </p><p>The Remote Gambling Association (RGA) is currently developing the online multi-operator self-exclusion scheme on behalf of the online sector.</p>","Bexleyheath and Crayford","David Evennett","40754","2016-06-27T14:39:17.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525558/answer","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525558/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525558/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-06-15","Gambling: Internet","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, whether a decision has been made by the Gambling Commission, his Department and the Remote Gambling Association about who will manage the online multi-operator self-exclusion scheme when it is established.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","40755"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525559","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-06-27","<p>The Digital Economy Bill will be introduced to Parliament shortly.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-06-27T15:44:43.813Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525559/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525559/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525559/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-06-15","Digital Technology","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what the timetable is for the Digital Economy Bill.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","40758"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525560","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-28","<p>The EU Battlegroup concept has Lead Nations on standby for six month periods. The UK was an EU Battlegroup Lead Nation from July to December 2013, and will be again from July to December 2016. The total number of UK personnel involved is 2,330. They remain under national control and direction at all times.</p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier",,"2016-06-28T15:11:55.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525560/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525560/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525560/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-06-15","EU Battlegroups","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what involvement UK armed forces have had with EU battle groups in the last three years; and how many UK armed forces personnel the Government has pledged to commit to those groups.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","40712"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525561","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-27","<table><tbody><tr><td colspan="2" rowspan="5"><p> </p></td><td colspan="6" rowspan="5"><p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given by my noble Friend the Minister of State for Defence, Earl Howe to the noble Lord, Lord Campbell of Pittenweem in the House of Lords to Question HL5630 on 8 February 2016. The Type 45 Destroyers were designed for world-wide operations, from sub-Arctic to extreme tropical environments and continue to operate effectively in the Persian Gulf and South Atlantic at all times of the year.</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-06-27T15:50:23.983Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525561/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525561/answer","Hansard Extract 8 Februry 2016 HL5630.docx","Type 45 Destroyers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525561/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-06-15","Type 45 Destroyers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will eliminate the cost of adapting Type 45 destroyers to operate in warm waters.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","40706"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525562","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-27","<p>The main investment decision on the UK's Maritime Patrol Aircraft programme has not yet been taken by Ministers, and no contracts have been placed to procure the P-8 Poseidon aircraft. No maintenance activity has therefore taken place on a British P-8 Poseidon aircraft.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-06-27T15:44:25.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525562/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525562/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525562/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-06-15","Maritime Patrol Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what proportion of ongoing maintenance on the UK P-8 Poseidon has been conducted in the US under US International Traffic in Arms Regulations.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","40672"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525563","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-27","<p>The current value of contracts between the Ministry of Defence and Boeing and Boeing Defence UK Ltd is approximately £665.75 million and £2.49 billion respectively. Contracts are also held with the Boeing subsidiaries Aviation Training International Ltd and Jeppesen UK Ltd amounting to £415.91 million and £6.59 million respectively.</p><p>The proportion of work by value carried out in the UK is around 53 per cent. This figure is based on direct contracts where the location of work code indicates that work is undertaken in the UK.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-06-27T15:45:30.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525563/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525563/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525563/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-06-15","Boeing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the current value of contracts is between his Department and Boeing and Boeing UK; and what proportion of work under those contracts is carried out in the UK.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","40670"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525564","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-27","<p>The Department intends to bring the P-8A into service without significant modification to ensure the delivery of operational capability as soon as is practicable. There are no current plans to integrate Stormshadow or other UK manufactured weapons onto the aircraft.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-06-27T15:30:44.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525564/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525564/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525564/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-06-15","Maritime Patrol Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether the P-8 Poseidon will be capable of carrying UK Storm Shadow and other manufactured munitions.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","40671"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525565","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-27","<p>The main investment decision on the UK's Maritime Patrol Aircraft programme has not yet been taken by Ministers and the initital support costs of the programme have not therefore been determined.</p><p>The Department is working with the US Department of Defense and Boeing on the route to contract for the programme. These negotiations will determine what elements of the programme could result in UK industrial participation.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-06-27T15:30:04.07Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525565/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525565/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525565/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-06-15","Maritime Patrol Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the cost of the UK P-8 Poseidon programme is; and what proportion of work share under that programme will be delivered through the UK defence industry.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","40673"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525566","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-27","<p>The main investment decision on the UK's Maritime Patrol Aircraft programme has not yet been taken by Ministers and the date at which the aircraft will be brought into service has yet to be determined. As the Prime Minister set out during last year's Strategic Defence and Security Review, however, at least three of the aircraft will be in place by the end of the current Parliament.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-06-27T15:44:57.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525566/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525566/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525566/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-06-15","Maritime Patrol Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what he plans the UK operational in-service date for the P-8 Poseidon will be.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","40684"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525567","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-28","<p>The Ministry of Defence (MOD) provides Service personnel with a range of educational, learning and development opportunities with our Learning Centres employing English and mathematics tutors who are employed to teach in numeracy and literacy. Over 95% of recruits are enrolled into an Apprenticeship Programme each year, regardless of their age, which ensures that Service personnel gain a Level 2 in numeracy and literacy. This is the equivalent of a GCSE.</p><p>It is an Ofsted goal that we encourage our people to achieve maths and English GCSE. The Ministry of Defence does actively encourage our Personnel to gain GCSE maths and English, and provides many opportunities for them to do this in their career with classes run in learning and development centres using part time Service instructors; or using distance learning programmes for exams sat on operational units and in shore bases.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-06-28T15:12:35.073Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525567/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525567/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525567/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-06-15","Armed Forces: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that armed forces recruits aged between 16 and 19 without a GCSE in mathematics or English are prepared for later life outside the armed forces.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","40822"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525568","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-28","<p>Following the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015, the Ministry of Defence project team are working with Air Tanker Ltd and their supplier, Airbus Defence and Space, on the Voyager enhanced cabin fit and are on target to deliver this in July 2016.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-06-28T15:03:13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525568/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525568/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525568/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-06-15","Future Strategic Tanker Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what progress has been made on the upgrade of a Voyager aircraft for transporting senior Ministers; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","40743"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525569","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-06-28","<p>Since becoming a signatory to the Oslo Convention on Cluster Munitions it is now unlawful for the UK to use cluster munitions under any circumstances.</p><p>For those states not currently a signatory to the Oslo Convention then the use of cluster munitions may be legitimate provided that they are used within the clearly defined limitations of International Humanitarian Law.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-06-28T15:09:58.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525569/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525569/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/525569/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-06-15","Cluster Munitions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether his Department considers that the use of cluster munitions is always unlawful under international humanitarian law because of their indiscriminate nature.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","40776"
